<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🤖 AI001 Week 5 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Iteration — The First Result Is Never Final · <strong>Course:</strong> AI Coding with Replit Agent · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>The AI's first try is almost never perfect — and that is normal. This week you learn to <strong>iterate</strong>: instead of deleting everything and starting over, you say "change just this one part." Good iteration prompts are specific and often include "keep this part the same."</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each iteration prompt. Before the AI changes anything, write what you expect to change — and what should stay the same.</p>
<pre><code>This is bad. Start over.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What happens to the parts you already liked? Is starting over a good idea here?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>Change the bottom 'submit' button from orange to green.
Leave everything else the same.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which part changes? Which parts stay? Why is "leave everything else the same" useful?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>Make the title bigger and brighter, and move the menu
to the top. Keep the photo where it is.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>List every change this asks for, and the one thing it protects.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Weak Prompt 🐛</h2>
<p>Each iteration prompt below is too vague or too risky. Read what the student <strong>wanted</strong>, then rewrite it so the AI changes exactly the right thing.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt A</strong> — The student liked the page but wanted the <strong>title color brighter</strong>. They typed:</p>
<pre><code>Make it better.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> "better" tells the AI nothing. Name the exact part and the exact change.</p>
<p><strong>Write a clear iteration prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was the first one risky?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Prompt B</strong> — The student wanted <strong>two cards merged into one</strong>, but everything else kept.</p>
<pre><code>Fix the cards.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> say which cards and what "fix" means. Protect the rest.</p>
<p><strong>Write a clear iteration prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was the first one risky?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Prompt C</strong> — The student liked the hero section a lot, but the AI keeps changing it on every edit.</p>
<pre><code>Make the footer dark.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> this prompt is fine, but add a line that protects the hero section so the AI stops touching it.</p>
<p><strong>Write an improved iteration prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does protecting a part help?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Iterate on a Project 📸</h2>
<p>Open one of your earlier projects (or build a quick one). Write <strong>several</strong> "change just this part" prompts to raise its quality. After each one, look at the result before writing the next.</p>
<p>When you finish, send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of the improved project, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I started with a project that …</p>
<p>My first change prompt asked the AI to …</p>
<p>I kept one part the same by saying …</p>
<p>One change did not work, so I …</p>
<p>The project got better because …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Log Your Changes 🗒️</h2>
<p>Write each iteration prompt you used, with <strong>one line</strong> saying what it changed. This log is part of your homework.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Change 1 — prompt: … → it changed: …</p>
<p>Change 2 — prompt: … → it changed: …</p>
<p>Change 3 — prompt: … → it changed: …</p>
<p>Change 4 — prompt: … → it changed: …</p>
<p>Change 5 — prompt: … → it changed: …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + a photo (or video) of your improved project + your change log to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
